parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving on the highway. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, making it difficult to stop or maneuver the vehicle.
symptoms: often stuck at a speed of around 40mph. The transmission may hesitate or slip
causing the vehicle to jerk or stutter. In some cases
the transmission may fail to operate altogether
leaving the vehicle unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or catching can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving on the highway. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, making it difficult to stop or maneuver the vehicle.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to hesitate or jerk. The vehicle may fail to accelerate
even when the RPMs increase. In some cases
the transmission may require the vehicle to come to a complete stop before it can "catch" and continue operating normally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues can cause the navigation, stereo, and console to shut off randomly, leading to a loss of critical systems while driving. This can increase the risk of accidents, especially if the driver is distracted or unable to access important information.
symptoms: often while driving. The volume knob may become inoperable
and other electrical systems may be affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust fumes inside the vehicle can cause nausea, sleepiness, and headaches, making it difficult for the driver to operate the vehicle safely. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Exhaust fumes permeate the interior of the vehicle
especially when the AC/heat/defrost is on. The smell can be overwhelming
causing discomfort and distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconsistent airbag deployment can lead to unnecessary injuries or failure to deploy in situations where it is necessary, compromising passenger safety.
symptoms: Unwanted airbag deployment in low-impact situations
failure to deploy in high-impact situations
airbag warning light illumination without a passenger present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty airbag sensors can cause airbags to deploy unnecessarily or fail to deploy in critical situations, putting passengers at risk of injury.
symptoms: failure to deploy in high-impact situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the brakes can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as experienced by the complainant who suffered a concussion and minor injuries.
symptoms: swirling or loss of control on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and become difficult to control, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: inability to move or accelerate above a certain speed
ABS light blinking on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of suspension and steering components can cause the vehicle to become unstable and difficult to control, leading to accidents or loss of control.
